\faDiamond\ \textlcsc{ \textcolor{dgreen}{\Large \textbf{Study Check}} }\\
For the reaction:
\begin{center}\ce{    H2_{(g)}  + 1/2 O2_{(g)} ->  H2O_{(g)}}\end{center}
we have that $\Delta H_{R}^{\circ}$ is -250kJ/mol and $\Delta S_{R}^{\circ}$ is -58J/mol. Calculate the entropy change on the system, its surroundings and the overall universe at 289K.\\

 \providetoggle{long}\settoggle{long}{true}\iftoggle{long}{}{\begin{flushright} \mytriangleright{dgreen}\small
Answer:  $\Delta S_{surr}=838$J/mol, $\Delta S_{univ}=781$J/mol 
 \end{flushright} }
